What was my question now?

00:40:08.505 --> 00:40:11.000
I loved your book,
your first book.

00:40:11.000 --> 00:40:15.010
I'm one of these goal-setting
people too.

00:40:15.010 --> 00:40:18.290
And I was fascinated/
overwhelmed by the fact that

00:40:18.290 --> 00:40:21.840
you added a new goal
every month.

00:40:21.840 --> 00:40:22.712
Am I correct?

00:40:22.712 --> 00:40:25.310
GRETCHEN RUBIN: Yeah, Yeah.

00:40:25.310 --> 00:40:31.420
AUDIENCE: So after the year was
over, how much did you end

00:40:31.420 --> 00:40:33.996
up actually holding onto them?

00:40:33.996 --> 00:40:35.046
What were the most
important ones?

00:40:35.046 --> 00:40:37.810
GRETCHEN RUBIN: So the question
is everything was

00:40:37.810 --> 00:40:40.530
cumulative, so at the end of
the whole thing with both

00:40:40.530 --> 00:40:42.240
projects how much
did I hang onto?

00:40:42.240 --> 00:40:45.190
I mean the fact I do almost
all of it still.

00:40:45.190 --> 00:40:46.740
Because it really all
makes me happier.

00:40:46.740 --> 00:40:48.810
And most of the things don't
take a lot of time

00:40:48.810 --> 00:40:50.670
or energy to do.

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:53.460
I mean there's kind of this
mental work of deciding to do

00:40:53.460 --> 00:40:57.370
it, and sticking to it, but
they don't-- so almost

00:40:57.370 --> 00:41:00.470
everything I do.

00:41:00.470 --> 00:41:02.000
Now, I mean, I did it in a very

00:41:02.000 --> 00:41:03.350
over-the-top way, clearly.

00:41:03.350 --> 00:41:05.350
So the idea is I'm trying
out all these things so

00:41:05.350 --> 00:41:06.150
you don't have to.

00:41:06.150 --> 00:41:09.960
So most people are not doing
like 100, 200 resolutions a

00:41:09.960 --> 00:41:12.230
day the way I am.

00:41:12.230 --> 00:41:14.593
But I think they're
reinforcing.

00:41:17.730 --> 00:41:20.100
I mean I'm very conscious of the
fact that I'm happier when

00:41:20.100 --> 00:41:21.400
I behave a certain
way, or when I

00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:23.070
follow certain practices.

00:41:23.070 --> 00:41:26.300
And so then that also helps
me feel motivated

00:41:26.300 --> 00:41:26.850
to stick with it.

00:41:26.850 --> 00:41:30.600
Because I know that it actually
has an effect, and

00:41:30.600 --> 00:41:31.830
really does make me happier.

00:41:31.830 --> 00:41:34.045
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]?

00:41:34.045 --> 00:41:36.320
GRETCHEN RUBIN: OK, so this is
