to the past and tell myself?

00:47:36.440 --> 00:47:38.740
I would take it back to that
point that I made earlier

00:47:38.740 --> 00:47:41.820
about be Gretchen.

00:47:41.820 --> 00:47:43.210
That's another splendid truth.

00:47:43.210 --> 00:47:46.720
Is we can build a happy life
only on the foundation of our

00:47:46.720 --> 00:47:50.060
own nature, our own values,
and our own interests.

00:47:50.060 --> 00:47:53.980
And I'm just one of these people
who spent a lot of time

00:47:53.980 --> 00:47:58.370
thinking or being swayed by the
way I thought I ought to

00:47:58.370 --> 00:48:00.670
be, or the way I wish I were,
the way other people thought I

00:48:00.670 --> 00:48:03.260
ought to be.

00:48:03.260 --> 00:48:08.450
And I think that it's really by
trying to figure out well

00:48:08.450 --> 00:48:09.350
is this right for me?

00:48:09.350 --> 00:48:10.370
Is this something
that I value?

00:48:10.370 --> 00:48:11.520
Is this something I'm
interested in?

00:48:11.520 --> 00:48:12.770
Does this reflect my nature?

00:48:15.330 --> 00:48:17.880
I wish I'd thought about that
much harder, much earlier.

00:48:17.880 --> 00:48:19.270
Everything ended
up fine for me.

00:48:19.270 --> 00:48:20.355
I mean that's the thing
about drift.

00:48:20.355 --> 00:48:21.570
Drifting into something
like law school.

00:48:21.570 --> 00:48:22.750
Sometimes it works out fine.

00:48:22.750 --> 00:48:24.180
And that's dangerous right?

00:48:24.180 --> 00:48:25.940
Because that's what makes it
even more tricky, because

00:48:25.940 --> 00:48:27.780
maybe it'll all work
out in the end.

00:48:27.780 --> 00:48:29.450
Don't count on it.

00:48:29.450 --> 00:48:30.750
So it all worked out.

00:48:30.750 --> 00:48:32.480
I'm glad, I'm happy
about everything

00:48:32.480 --> 00:48:33.140
that happened to me.

00:48:33.140 --> 00:48:35.340
But I didn't do it mindfully,
I didn't do it as an

00:48:35.340 --> 00:48:38.310
expression of what was
true about me.

00:48:38.310 --> 00:48:41.240
And I wish that I had
done if for that.

00:48:41.240 --> 00:48:42.146
Yeah?

00:48:42.146 --> 00:48:43.676
AUDIENCE: It seems like you
really good about being

00:48:43.676 --> 00:48:46.190
systematic about things.

00:48:46.190 --> 00:48:49.030
What ways would you go about
thinking about a framework or

00:48:49.030 --> 00:48:53.170
discovering what those things
are if you're not super clear

00:48:53.170 --> 00:48:53.490
about them?

00:48:53.490 --> 00:48:55.340
GRETCHEN RUBIN: That is
an excellent question.

00:48:55.340 --> 00:48:57.120
And in fact, for this new book
that I'm working on about

00:48:57.120 --> 00:48:59.090
habits I have this section that
I'm working on that's

00:48:59.090 --> 00:49:01.140
called quiz for self
knowledge.

00:49:01.140 --> 00:49:03.580
And it's just every time I think
about a question that I

00:49:03.580 --> 00:49:05.800
think you need to ask-- like are
you a morning person or a

00:49:05.800 --> 00:49:06.640
night person?

00:49:06.640 --> 00:49:08.910
This is really important
to know.

00:49:08.910 --> 00:49:10.470
Are you an abstainer
or moderator?

00:49:10.470 --> 00:49:12.700
Which is something I talk
about in my book.

00:49:12.700 --> 00:49:17.560
Are you spurred on by
competition, or are you

00:49:17.560 --> 00:49:21.180
unspurred on by competition?

00:49:21.180 --> 00:49:25.130
Do you feel very
self conscious?

00:49:25.130 --> 00:49:26.610
There's a lot of questions.

00:49:26.610 --> 00:49:30.820
So it's a very, very large
issue, and I've been thinking

00:49:30.820 --> 00:49:35.620
about how to systematically
figure out how would you

00:49:35.620 --> 00:49:38.920
figure that out without spending
thousands of dollars

00:49:38.920 --> 00:49:41.420
in therapy?

00:49:41.420 --> 00:49:44.440
So I don't have an easy question
other than to just

00:49:44.440 --> 00:49:47.550
constantly ask that, but I do
feel like I'm trying to

00:49:47.550 --> 00:49:50.030
identify sets of questions.

00:49:50.030 --> 00:49:54.540
So to help spur that kind
of self reflection.

00:49:54.540 --> 00:49:58.040
For me I find that it's from
reading other people.

00:49:58.040 --> 00:49:59.420
Like reading Samuel Johnson,
which is why

00:49:59.420 --> 00:50:01.230
mention him in my subtitle.

00:50:01.230 --> 00:50:02.860
When I read Samuel Johnson
I feel like I

00:50:02.860 --> 00:50:03.780
understand myself better.

00:50:03.780 --> 00:50:06.090
He just says things and I'm
like, OK, I get it.

00:50:06.090 --> 00:50:09.960
Somehow he's able to shine
a spotlight that helps me

00:50:09.960 --> 00:50:10.750
understand myself.

00:50:10.750 --> 00:50:14.480
So often by reading I feel like
some things resonate, but

00:50:14.480 --> 00:50:18.830
it seems like there should be
other ways to do it too.

